      "author": "davidgolding",
      "description": "This release formally rolls out **Script Mode**, providing an entirely distinct interface constraint optimized exclusively for industry-standard Screenwriting functionality without sacrificing Colophon's premium visual aesthetics.\r\n\r\n### Screenplay Integration \r\n*   **Script Mode Un-Paused**: Documents can now dynamically toggle between standard *Manuscript Mode* and the highly-controlled *Script Mode* via your primary view pane menu or command palette (`Colophon: Switch Mode`).\r\n*   **Aggressive Format Restraints**: In Script Mode, the Tiptap schema completely locks you into Screenwriting syntax (`script-scene`, `script-action`, `script-character`, `script-parenthetical`, `script-dialogue`, `script-transition`). Empty or \"self-healing\" documents will intelligently fall back to resolving cursor positions with `action` lines rather than prose bodies.\r\n\r\n### Fountain Export Engine\r\n*   Colophon now officially generates pure, pristine [Fountain](https://fountain.io/) markup files.\r\n*   Once toggled into *Script Mode*, the core toolbars natively swap the DOCX exporter out for a dedicated **Export to Fountain (.fountain)** generation action.\r\n*   The architecture automatically validates syntax integrity behind the scenes (e.g. dropping forced `.` periods before scenes lacking `INT/EXT`, forcing `@` wrappers before characters, maintaining rigid line-breaks, etc.) entirely silently. \r\n\r\n### UI / UX Enhancements\r\n*   **Split Settings Engine**: The core configuration menu for custom blocks now dynamically categorizes attributes strictly by their Manuscript vs Script status and sorts dependencies alphabetically.\r\n*   **Formatting Guardrails**: Eliminated `footnote`, `footnote-symbol`, and `footnote-marker` blocks from rendering in the root editing dropdown to prevent users from accidentally applying formatting logic intended strictly for margin annotations. \r\n\r\n### Under the Hood\r\n*   Bumped the core Tiptap engine to `v3.22.3`.",
      "downloadCount": 2,
      "draft": false,
